Reasoning: The paper focuses on developing a parallel algorithm and scalable implementation for genome analysis, specifically for long read sequencing data. This involves addressing issues of increasing parallelism, minimizing communication, constraining memory footprint, and ensuring good load balance. These topics are typically covered in the following arXiv CS sub-categories: Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
